01/04/2011
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Prime Minister David Cameron on Thursday (March 31s) reassured his visiting counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan of London's support for Turkey's EU bid. 
The two officials discussed international efforts to protect civilians in Libya. 
Erdogan voiced his opposition to the idea of arming Libyan rebels. 
He warned that such a move could be conducive to terrorism. 
(Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Zaman, World Bulletin - 31/03/11)
